  <a name="payment-exclusivity" class="anchor"></a>
  <div class="answers">
    <h4>Payment/Exclusivity&nbsp;&uarr;<a href="#top" class="top">return to top</a></h4>
    <h5>How much does a instructor make?</h5>

    <p>Firehoze pays a base royalty rate of 50% from the revenue of each lesson purchased for Exclusive instructors and
      25% for Non-exclusive instructors.</p>

    <h5>How do I get paid and how often?</h5>

    <p>Firehoze mails checks monthly on balances over $50. You may request a payment even if your balance is less than
      $50, but a $2 handling fee will be assessed. Please allow 1-2 weeks for processing.</p>

    <h5>How long am I committed?</h5>

    <p>Don't worry, if you change your mind, just let us know anytime before you've received 30 days in advance by email
      (<a href="javascript:location='mailto:\u0073\u0075\u0070\u0070\u006f\u0072\u0074\u0040\u0066\u0069\u0072\u0065\u0068\u006f\u007a\u0065\u002e\u0063\u006f\u006d';void 0">
        <script type="text/javascript">document.write('\u0073\u0075\u0070\u0070\u006f\u0072\u0074\u0040\u0066\u0069\u0072\u0065\u0068\u006f\u007a\u0065\u002e\u0063\u006f\u006d')</script>
      </a>) and we'll change your commission structure.
    </p>

    <h5>What does it mean to be an Exclusive instructor?</h5>

    <p>Exclusivity means your lessons and the associated content may not be sold or given away for free to other sites
      or businesses including on the instructor's site.</p>

    <h5>How can I see how much money I've made?</h5>

    <p>You can find this information in your account information. Click on the <%= account_settings_link %> link at the
      top of the page. Then go to the 'Payment History' tab to see the lessons of yours that have been purchased by
      other Firehoze users and how much you've made from them.</p>
  </div>

  <a name="privacy" class="anchor"></a>
  <div class="answers">
    <h4>Privacy&nbsp;&uarr;<a href="#top" class="top">return to top</a></h4>
    <h5>Do you share emails addresses?</h5>

    <p>Nope, never. Even if you choose to allow other Firehoze users to contact you via email, those users will never
      see your actual email address.</p>

    <h5>Do you sell information?</h5>

    <p>Only if they offer us a lot of money. Okay, kidding, we don't...we hate having our information sold too.</p>

    <h5>Can people contact me directly?</h5>

    <p>Only if you want them to. The default is 'no' but to change this setting go to <%= account_settings_link %> at
      the top of the page and click on the 'Privacy' tab to make your selection.</p>

    <h5>How can I see what my public profile is?</h5>

    <p>You can look at this by going into your <%= account_settings_link %>, clicking on the 'Profile' tab. At the top
      of the page you'll see a link with the option 'view your public profile here'.</p>
  </div>

  <a name="beta-site" class="anchor"></a>
  <div class="answers">
    <h4>Beta Site&nbsp;&uarr;<a href="#top" class="top">return to top</a></h4>
    <h5>Is this really the final site?</h5>

    <p>Ahh...no. Are you kidding?! It's pretty ugg-leey. But the functionality should be working so if any functionality
      doesn't seem to work, definitely let us know. You can do this a few ways – email us directly or go to the
      'Feedback' tab and let us know there.</p>

    <h5>So, why doesn’t your site look very spiffy?</h5>

    <p>Well, prioritization...and while we have superstar developers, they're still stuck by physics and that darn 24
      hour day. So top priority is getting great content loaded and tagged so we wanted to get something into your hands
      so you only had to load content once.</p>

    <h5>Why is English my only choice in the language drop-down?</h5>

    <p>English is just the beginning...but we're still in 'beginning' stage. Want to influence what the next languages
      should be? Go to our 'Feedback' button on the right of the page and vote on what you'd like to see next. And if
      you'd be interested in helping us translate the site into another language, we'd love to know that as well.</p>

    <h5>What browsers are supported?</h5>

    <p>The big ones at the moment but more to come. Firefox 3.0 and higher, InternetExplorer 6.x and higher, Safari,
      Chrome. Other
      browsers and versions may work just fine, but we don't guarantee it. If there's a browser you think we should
      support but don't, we'd love to hear from you.</p>
  </div>

  <a name="contributing-uploading-lessons" class="anchor"></a>
  <div class="answers">
    <h4>Contributing/Uploading Lessons&nbsp;&uarr;<a href="#top" class="top">return to top</a></h4>
    <h5>How do I become an instructor ?</h5>

    <p>Easily...</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Go to <%= account_settings_link %>.</li>
      <li>Select the Instructor tab and click the button to walk through the Instructor Signup Wizard.</li>
      <li>Complete all steps in the wizard.</li>
      <li>Start teaching!</li>
    </ol>

    <h5>Why give me the option to provide free downloads when I post a lesson?</h5>

    <p>Free downloads give you the chance to build up some ratings and reviews before users have to purchase your
      lesson. It can be a good way to your reputation, activity and traction on the site.</p>


    <h5>How do I pull or delete a lesson?</h5>

    <p>Shoot us an email
      (<a href="javascript:location='mailto:\u0073\u0075\u0070\u0070\u006f\u0072\u0074\u0040\u0066\u0069\u0072\u0065\u0068\u006f\u007a\u0065\u002e\u0063\u006f\u006d';void 0">
        <script type="text/javascript">document.write('\u0073\u0075\u0070\u0070\u006f\u0072\u0074\u0040\u0066\u0069\u0072\u0065\u0068\u006f\u007a\u0065\u002e\u0063\u006f\u006d')</script>
      </a>) providing your user name and the title of the tutorial you'd like pulled. When we delete you're lesson, we
      will also delete all of the associated content including the lesson video, synopsis, notes, tags, reviews and
      ratings.
    </p>

    <h5>What happens when I request a lesson to be pulled? What happens to my ratings and reviews when I pull a
      lesson?</h5>

    <p>We'll pull the lesson l and all of the associated content including the lesson video, synopsis, notes, tags,
      reviews, discussion comments and ratings.</p>

    <h5>What are the specs required for lesson videos to be uploaded?</h5>

    <p>Files must be less than 500 MB. We support the following file formats:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>MPEG-1, MPEG-2, H.263, H.264</li>
      <li>All MPEG-4 implementations (Xvid, 3vix, etc.)</li>
      <li>AVI</li>
      <li>.MOV</li>
      <li>MP4</li>
      <li>.MPG, .VOB (unencrypted VOBs only)</li>
      <li>Windows Media/VC-1</li>
      <li>3GP/3G2</li>
      <li>Ogg Theora</li>
      <li>MJPEG</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <a name="recording" class="anchor"></a>
  <div class="answers">
    <h4>Recording&nbsp;&uarr;<a href="#top" class="top">return to top</a></h4>
    <h5>What are some options for recording lessons?</h5>
    <ol>
      <li>Use a webcam + screen capture software</li>
      <ol>
        <li type=a>If you are recording yourself writing on paper, we recommend a dark color of marker, like a medium
          Sharpie, so it's readable.
        </li>
        <li type=a>If using Jing Pro or ScreenToaster for screen capture, they can record right from the webcam (whatever
          it sees will be recorded)
        </li>
      </ol>
      <li>Use a slide presentation + screen capture software</li>
      <li>Use a graphic tablet + screen capture software</li>
      <p>Program options when using a tablet</p>
      <ol>
        <li type=a><strong>For PCs</strong>, use Windows Journal</li>
        <ol>
          <li type=i>If you MS Vista, you should already have this program.</li>
          <li type=i>If you have XP, you may have it or be able to download it. It may also come with your tablet.</li>
        </ol>
        <li type=a><strong>For Macs</strong>, use inkBook
          (<a href="http://mac.rbytes.net/cat/mac/utilities/inkbook/">http://mac.rbytes.net/cat/mac/utilities/inkbook</a>)
          or TabletDraw
          (<a href="http://www.apple.com/downloads/macosx/imaging_3d/tabletdraw.html">http://www.apple.com/downloads/macosx/imaging_3d/tabletdraw.html</a>)
        </li>
        <li type=a><strong>For both PCs and Macs</strong>, Corel Paint is an option.</li>
      </ol>
      <li>Use a video camera</li>
      <ol>
        <li type=a>Record your writing on a whiteboard</li>
        <ol>
          <li type=i>Keep in mind, it's the lesson that is of interest so try to focus on the whiteboard and not the
            surrounding area.
          </li>
          <li type=i>Light marker colors can be hard to see so we suggest you test any colors you plan on using to make
            sure your viewers will be able to see them clearly.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <li type=a>Record your writing on chalkboard (hey, there have to be a few of these left in the world!)</li>
      </ol>
    </ol>

    <h5>What tools are available for capturing videos?</h5>

    <p>
      <strong><i>Jing Pro (<a href="http://www.jingproject.com/pro/">http://www.jingproject.com/pro/</a>)</i></strong>
    </p>

    <p>Best for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Those looking for something easy to use and intuitive</li>
      <li>Further editing will not be preformed as it allows for live swapping of a web cam view of the speaker with a
        capture frame.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>Pros:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Easy to use</li>
      <li>Clean, user-friendly interface</li>
      <li>Well-supported with video tutorials since made by prominent software provider</li>
      <li>Live swapping of a web cam view of the speaker with a capture frame</li>
      <li>Native MP4 encoding</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Cons:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Can only capture up to 5 min video</li>
      <li>Costs $15 per year</li>
      <li>Limited output options -- it only allows for SWF and MP4, no compression codec option</li>
      <li>Audio can sound soft or garbled so a quiet space is needed</li>
    </ul>


    <strong><i>CamStudio (<a href="http://camstudio.org/">http://camstudio.org/</a>)</i></strong>

    <p>Best for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Those looking for features to support a higher level of video production</li>
      <li>Desire to do further editing of captured video</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Pros:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Free and open source</li>
      <li>More expansive feature set – codec choice, intelligent capture moving the frame to follow the cursor during
        capture
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>Cons:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>User interface isn't terribly pretty</li>
      <li>Additional features can make for a slower learning curve</li>
    </ul>

    <strong><i>ScreenToaster (<a href="http://www.screentoaster.com/)">http://www.screentoaster.com/)</a></i></strong>

    <p>Best for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Those looking for something easy to use and intuitive</li>
      <li>Option to redub your video after capture</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Pros:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Free</li>
      <li>No software to download</li>
      <li>More intelligent audio than Jing – allows the user to select a target playback rate and redub the audio post
        capture
      </li>
      <li>Captures live from a webcam and show the video as a picture in picture in the corner of the screen capture.</li>
      <li>Output to .mov (QuickTime)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Cons</p>
    <ul>
      <li>User interface isn't as elegant as Jing</li>
      <li>Limited post-editing options</li>
      <li>No compression options</li>
    </ul>

