  <a name="buying-lessons" class="anchor"></a>
  <div class="answers">
    <h4>Buying Lessons/Credits&nbsp;&uarr;<a href="#top" class="top">return to top</a></h4>
    <h5>How do I purchase lessons from your site?</h5>

    <p>All you need to do is by one or more credit(s) to purchase tutorials. You can easily purchase credits by clicking
      on the 'Purchase Credits' link in the upper right hand of your screen.</p>

    <h5>Why do you use credits?</h5>

    <p>To make your browsing and buying experience easier. It would be a pain to have to do a full shopping cart
      checkout and specify your credit card each time you want to watch a lesson. Buying a bunch of credits makes it
      easier to quickly view lessons when you find one you want.</p>

    <p>Oh yeah, also, if all credit card transactions were 99 cents each, the credit card companies would kill us on
      fees and we'd have to charge more for the lessons.</p>

    <h5>Where are my receipts/download history?</h5>

    <p>You can find all of this information in your account information. Click on the <%= account_settings_link %> link
      at the top of the page. Then go to the 'Order History' tab to see them.</p>

    <h5>How can I give credits to someone else?</h5>

    <p>A gift certificate is the best and easiest way to do this.</p>

    <h5>Where are my receipts/download history?</h5>

    <p>Your download history is stored in your account information. Click on the ‘<%= account_settings_link %>’ at the
      top of the site. Then click the ‘Credit History’ tab.</p>

    <h5>Do credits expire?</h5>

    <p>Credits will expire within a year if you don't log into Firehoze. All you have to do to keep your credits from
      expiring is log on at least once a year. Pretty simple, right?</p>

    <p>If you have credits that are about to expire, we'll warn you via email 30 days before they expire, just to remind
      you to log on to keep them alive.</p>
  </div>

  <a name="managing-my-account" class="anchor"></a>
  <div class="answers">
    <h4>Managing My Account&nbsp;&uarr;<a href="#top" class="top">return to top</a></h4>
    <h5>Where can I find a record of lessons I've purchased?</h5>

    <p>Your download history is stored in your account information. Click on the ‘<%= account_settings_link %>’ at the
      top of the site. Then click the ‘Credit History’ tab to see a list of all the download credits you've purchased
      and which ones you've redeemed for lessons.</p>

    <h5>Where can I see how many credits I have left?</h5>

    <p>You can find your remaining credits in the upper right hand of your screen.</p>

    <h5>How do I change my user name?</h5>

    <p>If you would like to change your user name, please contact us at
      <a href="javascript:location='mailto:\u0073\u0075\u0070\u0070\u006f\u0072\u0074\u0040\u0066\u0069\u0072\u0065\u0068\u006f\u007a\u0065\u002e\u0063\u006f\u006d';void 0">
        <script type="text/javascript">document.write('\u0073\u0075\u0070\u0070\u006f\u0072\u0074\u0040\u0066\u0069\u0072\u0065\u0068\u006f\u007a\u0065\u002e\u0063\u006f\u006d')</script>
      </a> with your existing user name and the new user name you would like to use.
    </p>

    <h5>How can I change my password?</h5>

    <p>To change your password, click on the ‘<%= account_settings_link %>’ link at the top of the site. Then go to the
      ‘Password’ tab.</p>

    <h5>How do I edit my email information?</h5>

    <p>To change your address or contact information, click on the ‘<%= account_settings_link %>’ link at the top of the
      site, then click on the 'Profile' tab.</p>

    <h5>How can I retrieve my password and/or member name?</h5>

    <p>Just click on the 'Forgot password 'link on the login page.</p>
